            "creation_date": 1417784432,
            "body": "<p>If the Room has other numeric attributes, then make the variables' names more specific. If the room number is the only numeric attribute I think that <code>room.getNumber()<\/code> is enough.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 27316480,
            "question_id": 27316365
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1ae0dbfb1930976b1ae2edd367bcf3b6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 3889856,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3220357,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3220357/slowy",
                "reputation": 81,
                "display_name": "slowy"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1417786356,
            "creation_date": 1417786356,
            "body": "<p>(Welcome to slowy's philosophical programming class)<\/p>\n\n<p>getNumber() may sound okay. But how does it look, when the room has ten more attributes? How does it look for someone else? What if you would have a Type Employee with an employeeNumber and a Reservation with a reservationNumber? How does the business talk about it? How would the label of a web-gui be named for this property?<\/p>\n\n<p>Keep in mind: <\/p>\n\n<p>1) Most of the time, it's better to name methods and variables in a way, so that it's easier to understand. If you name something, try to name it, so you don't have to comment it. If the variable is longer than your 24\" wide screen tft, well, something went horribly wrong hehe. In your case, I would have commented, that getNumber() will return the room number, just to make it perfectly clear. Not necessary otherwise.<\/p>\n\n<p>2) Consistency: If the business is talking about a room number, name it room number. From the member variables, to methods, to table columns. If possible. It makes everything easier. This includes methods like \"readRoomByRoomNumber()\" instead of \"readRoomByNumber()\". <\/p>\n\n<p>3) Naming of variables: Also declare \"Room room = new Room()\" and not \"Room r = new Room()\". So in the end: \"room.getRoomNumber\" is so much easier to read than \"r.getNumber()\" ;-)<\/p>\n\n<p>Hope this helps,\nregards,\nslowy<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 27317041,
            "question_id": 27316365
        }
    ],
